%Tutorial ------  Edit Macro PARA Parameters Reference Appendix  ------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
%1. Parameters that PARA remembers during an ISPF session :+

 %OL=nn   +Old Left side of the paragraph
 %OR=nn   +Old Right side of the paragraph
           The Old parameters tell PARA where to find the paragraph to b
           reformatted. The first time PARA executes during an ISPF sess
           the Old parameters normally default to the display columns on
           left and right sides of the screen. You will only change the
           parameters when :
            (1) You are editing a document wider than the screen size (i
                133 wide for a 3278 model 2, 80 columns wide).
            (2) Or, when there is textual material that you don't want t
                include on the left or right side of the paragraph to be
                reformatted.
+
+Enter%&EPF+to exit the tutorial and return to the PARA facility
+Hit%ENTER+to go on to the next tutorial panel
)INIT
  &EPF = PFK(END)
  IF (&EPF = &Z)
    &EPF = 'END'
  &D = TRUNC(&EPF,2)
  &DT = .TRAIL
  &D = TRUNC(&DT,1)
  IF (&D = '0')
    &DT = .TRAIL
    &EPF = 'PF&DT'
)PROC
  &ZCONT = PAJTPARB
)END
